\paragraph{LLMs as Knowledge Bases.}
[petroni-etal-2019-language] showed that 
LLM prompts can generate facts of knowledge-base style. 
The approach has been expanded
and refined in various ways (e.g., [DBLP:journals/tacl/JiangXAN20,shin-etal-2020-autoprompt,DBLP:conf/naacl/QinE21,DBLP:conf/www/ChenZXDYTHSC22]). 
These aim at precision, 
disregarding recall and the long tail.
Recent studies indicate that LLMs have major problems in dealing with long tail facts [DBLP:conf/emnlp/VeseliRKW23,DBLP:journals/corr/abs-2308-10168,singhania-etal-2023-extracting,DBLP:conf/icml/KandpalDRWR23].